cp||at|Although 2NT is not forcing, the phrase "highly invitational" is very important here. Too many players are eager to pass 2NT. This is wrong thinking. It is very rare, especially playing IMPs, where you will get a good result passing 2NT. The only time it is right is if your side can make exactly 2NT and not 3NT. There is much more upside to bidding 3NT (or 4 of a major with an appropriate hand) than passing. So I recommend the only time you pass is with 5 HCP or with a bad 6 HCP and no 5-card suit. You should strain to bid game on this auction.|
